main event: A witness observed a strange exhaust pattern in the sky at May Port, Florida on February 9, 1955.
interesting points: The exhaust appeared white and sharply defined, spanning 180 degrees in the area.
The object left no contrails, unlike other aircraft in the vicinity.
The sighting lasted for two time units (likely minutes or seconds).
The report suggests the object may have been a 'non-conventional' aircraft.
The document appears to be a Project Blue Book record card, indicating this was an official UFO investigation.
